@node "--arexx--" "hypertext.datatype/--arexx--"

    @{b}NAME@{ub}
        arexx interface -- hypertext.datatype ARexx commands

    @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
        The hypertext.datatype provides a own ARexx port for each object.
        It's name is the port name passed via @{"DTA_ARexxPortName" link "AG:SysInc/datatypes/datatypesclass.h/main" 191} plus a
        suffix of '.1' or if this port exists '.2' and so on.
        For example if you start MultiView with a hypertext object, MultiView
        passes "MULTIVIEW.1" for @{"DTA_ARexxPortName" link "AG:SysInc/datatypes/datatypesclass.h/main" 191} to the hypertext object.
        The hypertext object tries to open a port named "MULTIVIEW.1.1".

    @{b}AREXX COMMANDS@{ub}
        See a detailed list and description in the hypertext_dtc.hguide
        document.

    @{b}SEE ALSO@{ub}
        hypertext_dtc.hguide


@endnode
@node "--datasheet--" "hypertext.datatype/--datasheet--"

    @{b}NAME@{ub}
        hypertext.datatype -- hypertext base class datatype

    @{b}SUPERCLASS@{ub}
        datatypesclass

    @{b}DESCRIPTION@{ub}
        The hypertext datatype class implements all methods for layout,
        rendering and printing of hypertext and text objects. It supports
        searching within documents and embedding of other datatype objects.

        The following list gives an overview about the features of the
        hypertext datatype class :

        o embedding of other DataTypes objects (@{"DTM_DRAW" link "AG:SysInc/datatypes/datatypesclass.h/main" 282}).

          the hypertext.datatype supports embedding of other datatypes using
          the @{"DTM_DRAW" link "AG:SysInc/datatypes/datatypesclass.h/main" 282} method to render such objects. It's also possible to
          use a object multiple times in one document.

        o multiple fonts

          it supports more than one font in one document. Limit is only set
          by the available fonts and memory.

        o links to other DataTypes objects.

        o links to programs and ARexx-scripts

        o line separator like HTML <hr>

        o justification left,center,right

        o asyncron rendering (not in input task)

        o own ARexx port (See --arexx--)

        o a defined API

          see datatypes/hypertextclass.h and the following function
          description.

        o example HyperText subclass htdemo

          a full subclass implementation with source code is available to
          demonstrate the usage of the hypertext.datatype API.

    @{b}METHODS@{ub}
        @{"OM_NEW" link "OM_NEW"} -- Create a new hypertext object.

        @{"OM_GET" link "OM_GET"} -- Obtain the value of an attribute.

        @{"OM_SET" link "OM_SET"} -- Set the values of multiple attributes.

        @{"OM_UPDATE" link "OM_UPDATE"} -- Updates the values of multiple attributes.

        @{"OM_DISPOSE" link "OM_DISPOSE"} -- Dispose of a hypertext object and all of it's
            resources.

        @{"OM_NOTIFY" link "OM_NOTIFY"} -- Snoops the notification of some attributes.

        @{"GM_LAYOUT" link "GM_LAYOUT"} -- Layout the object and notify the application of the
            title and size.

        @{"GM_GOACTIVE" link "GM_GOACTIVE"} -- Tell the object to go active.

        @{"GM_HANDLEINPUT" link "GM_HANDLEINPUT"} -- Handle input.

        @{"GM_RENDER" link "GM_RENDER"} -- Cause the object to render. This is done asyncron, so
            input task sends only messages to the hypertext support process.
            This method overwrites the superclass @{"GM_RENDER" link "GM_RENDER"} method.

        @{"DTM_GOTO" link "DTM_GOTO"} -- Cause the object to load a other object or document.

        @{"DTM_TRIGGER" link "DTM_TRIGGER"} -- Trigger an event. Following are currently supported :

            @{"STM_PREV_FIELD" link "AG:SysInc/datatypes/datatypesclass.h/main" 372} -- Select previous field/link.

            @{"STM_NEXT_FIELD" link "AG:SysInc/datatypes/datatypesclass.h/main" 371} -- Select next field/link.

            @{"STM_ACTIVATE_FIELD" link "AG:SysInc/datatypes/datatypesclass.h/main" 373} -- Activate actual selected field/link. And
                execute the appropriate command. Like running a program,
                start a ARexx-script or load a new object.

            @{"STM_RETRACE" link "AG:SysInc/datatypes/datatypesclass.h/main" 367} -- Retrace to last visited node.

            @{"STM_CONTENTS" link "AG:SysInc/datatypes/datatypesclass.h/main" 365} -- Show contents node.

            @{"STM_INDEX" link "AG:SysInc/datatypes/datatypesclass.h/main" 366} -- Show index node.

            @{"STM_BROWSE_PREV" link "AG:SysInc/datatypes/datatypesclass.h/main" 368} -- Go to the logical previous node.

            @{"STM_BROWSE_NEXT" link "AG:SysInc/datatypes/datatypesclass.h/main" 369} -- Go to the logical next node.

        @{"DTM_REMOVEDTOBJECT" link "DTM_REMOVEDTOBJECT"} -- Used to clear internal cached variables. Then
            directly passed to superclass.

        @{"DTM_COPY" link "DTM_COPY"} -- Copies the current object or selected area to clipboard.

        @{"DTM_FRAMEBOX" link "DTM_FRAMEBOX"} -- Informs the application, which environment the object
            needs.

        @{"DTM_WRITE" link "DTM_WRITE"} -- Writes the contents of the current object to a file.

        @{"DTM_PRINT" link "DTM_PRINT"} -- Prints the current object.

        @{"DTM_SELECT" link "DTM_SELECT"} -- Selects a area of the current object.

        @{"DTM_CLEARSELECTED" link "DTM_CLEARSELECTED"} -- Clears the selected area.

        @{"HTDTM_LAYOUT" link "HTDTM_LAYOUT"} -- Layout the hypertext segments. Caclulate
            justifications and other dynamical layout parameters.

        @{"HTDTM_GETFONT" link "HTDTM_GETFONT"} -- Tries to open a specified font. The hypertext
            datatype handles all resource tracking, so that you can call this
            method much often without remembering the opened font.

        @{"HTDTM_OBTAINPEN" link "HTDTM_OBTAINPEN"} -- Tries to allocate a shared pen. The hypertext
            datatype handles all resource tracking.

        @{"HTDTM_OBTAIN" link "HTDTM_OBTAIN"} -- Obtain the hypertext object semaphore.

        @{"HTDTM_RELEASE" link "HTDTM_RELEASE"} -- Release the hypertext object semaphore.

        @{"HTDTM_ATTEMPT" link "HTDTM_ATTEMPT"} -- Attempt to obtain the hypertext object semaphore.

        @{"HTDTM_ALLOCVEC" link "HTDTM_ALLOCVEC"} -- Allocate a memory from the hypertext objects memory
            pool. Similar to @{"AllocVec()" link "exec/AllocVec()"}.

        @{"HTDTM_FREEVEC" link "HTDTM_FREEVEC"} -- Free memory allocatec by @{"HTDTM_ALLOCVEC" link "HTDTM_ALLOCVEC"}.

        @{"HTDTM_HTPROC" link "HTDTM_HTPROC"} -- Check if the current method is invoked on the separate
            hypertext object process. Note: If you overwrite some methods like
            @{"DTM_GOTO" link "DTM_GOTO"}, you have to check first if you are in that special
            process context, and if not you have to pass this method directly
            to superclass, so that this can signal the hypertext object
            process to do this method on its context. This strategy is needed
            to avoid problems with input task based method invocations.

        @{"HTDTM_RENDER" link "HTDTM_RENDER"} -- Render the hypertext object on its separate process.

        @{"HTDTM_LOADNODES" link "HTDTM_LOADNODES"} -- Tries to load all node informations from a
            database to avoid scanning the whole file.

        @{"HTDTM_SAVENODES" link "HTDTM_SAVENODES"} -- Save all node information to a database. Currently
            the node information is only saved in the documents icon.

        @{"HTDTM_SEARCH" link "HTDTM_SEARCH"} -- Searchs for occurence of the given pattern or string.
            NOTE: Only available in the registered version.

        @{"HTDTM_GUISEARCH" link "HTDTM_GUISEARCH"} -- Opens the search requester on a separate process
            and waits for input from the user.
            NOTE: Only available in the registered version.

        @{"HTDTM_EXPORT" link "HTDTM_EXPORT"} -- exports the current document to a specific format.
            NOTE: Only available in the registered version.

        @{"HTDTM_CONVATTRIB" link "HTDTM_CONVATTRIB"} -- used to convert additional HyperGuide style
            attributes during @{"ConvertAttributes()" link "ConvertAttributes()"} call.

